column7: Data are all from Brian Elliott, email correspondence 5/26/2020
There is a known discrepancy btwn B. Elliott's abundance totals and those calculated by Leon/Justin (e.g., troll catch 2018/2019)
This discrepancy is due to how to calc contributions; B. Elliot's method uses a different strata/area than the "preferred" by the MTA lab
For more information on this, emails from Eric Keller, 7/9/2020 summarize this.
In the opinion of JTP, Brian's calculations are better for estimating week-to-week contributions but possibly biased on an annual basis
For Sport (Freshwater) SWHS harvest estimate from Chilkat River drainage and Chilkat Lake only; 2019 estimate based on historical proportion of total run
For Subsistence, a portion (~16%) of total subsistence harvest occurs in Chilkat Inlet, assumed to be Chilkat coho.
